                    <title>Discharge Summaries</title>
                    <text>
                        <list styleCode="xTOC">
                            <item>
                                <caption>Britany Jane Harris, PA-C - 07/07/2019 1:35 PM EDT</caption>
                                <content ID="Note32">
                                    <content><content styleCode="xLabel">Formatting of this note is
                                        different from the original.</content><br />Patient Name: Elvira Valadez<br />
                                        Patient ID: 001234<br />
                                        Date of Admission: 2024-07-18<br />
                                        Date of Discharge: 2024-07-20<br />
                                        Attending Physician: Dr. Alice Williams<br />
                                        <br />
                                        Admission Diagnosis:<br />
                                        Community-Acquired Pneumonia (CAP)<br /><br />
                                        <br />
                                        Hospital Course:<br />
                                        Elvira Valadez was admitted with symptoms of fever, productive cough, and shortness of breath. Initial chest X-ray showed consolidation in the right lower lobe, confirming pneumonia. She was started on intravenous antibiotics, including ceftriaxone and azithromycin.
                                        <br />
                                        During her hospital stay, Jane improved significantly. Her fever subsided, and her cough decreased in frequency and severity. Repeat chest X-ray showed marked improvement. She was switched to oral antibiotics after five days and responded well.
                                        <br />
                                        Discharge Medications:<br />
                                        Amoxicillin 500 mg, orally, three times a day for 5 more days
                                        Acetaminophen 500 mg, orally, every 6 hours as needed for fever
                                        Albuterol inhaler, 2 puffs every 4-6 hours as needed for wheezing<br />
                                        Follow-up:<br />
                                        Follow up with primary care physician in 1 week
                                        Repeat chest X-ray in 4 weeks<br />
                                        Discharge Instructions:<br />
                                        Continue medications as prescribed
                                        Encourage fluid intake and rest
                                        Monitor for any signs of recurrence, such as fever or worsening cough</content>
                                    <br />
                                    <content styleCode="xLabel">Electronically signed by Maa Devi
                                        Abigail, MD at 07/20/2024 4:59 PM EDT</content>
                                    <br />
                                    <br />
                                    <content styleCode="xcellHeader">Associated attestation - Abigail,
                                        Maa Devi, MD - 07/20/2024 4:59 PM EDT</content>
                                    <br />
                                    <content><content styleCode="xLabel">Formatting of this note
                                        might be different from the original.</content><br />I
                                        independently saw and examined the patient and discussed
                                        with PA Williams and agree with assessment and plan as
                                        documented.</content>
                                    <br />
                                </content>
                            </item>
                        </list>
